  <section>
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>Web development is the process of building websites and applications that live on the internet. It involves a combination of design, programming, and database management to deliver seamless digital experiences. From small blogs to powerful web platforms, everything you interact with online is a product of web development.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Frontend Development</h2>
    <p>The frontend, also called the client-side, is what users interact with. It involves languages like HTML for content, CSS for layout and design, and JavaScript for interactivity. Frameworks such as React, Bootstrap, and Tailwind CSS help developers build sleek, responsive interfaces efficiently.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>HTML:</strong> Structures the content of a web page</li>
      <li><strong>CSS:</strong> Adds style, color, layout, and design</li>
      <li><strong>JavaScript:</strong> Makes the website interactive and dynamic</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Backend Development</h2>
    <p>The backend, or server-side, handles the logic, database interactions, authentication, and server configuration. It ensures data is correctly processed and securely stored. Common backend languages include Python, Node.js, PHP, Java, and Ruby.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Node.js:</strong> JavaScript runtime for backend</li>
      <li><strong>Django/Flask:</strong> Python frameworks for web apps</li>
      <li><strong>Express.js:</strong> Minimal and flexible Node.js framework</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Databases</h2>
    <p>Databases store all the data needed by the application. There are two main types: relational (SQL) and non-relational (NoSQL). The choice depends on the type and structure of data being handled.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>SQL Databases:</strong> MySQL, PostgreSQL - structured tables</li>
      <li><strong>NoSQL Databases:</strong> MongoDB, Firebase - flexible formats</li>
      <li>CRUD Operations: Create, Read, Update, Delete</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Full Stack Development</h2>
    <p>Full Stack Development combines both frontend and backend skills. Full Stack Developers can build complete web applications. A popular stack is the MERN Stack:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>MongoDB:</strong> NoSQL database</li>
      <li><strong>Express.js:</strong> Backend framework</li>
      <li><strong>React:</strong> Frontend library</li>
      <li><strong>Node.js:</strong> Backend runtime</li>
    </ul>
